lash.com/photo-1712576752855-bf4721d76a86?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIYW5vaSUyME9sZCUyMFF1YXJ0ZXIlMjBzdHJlZXQlMjBWaWV0bmFtfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM4ODE1ODV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Elric Pxl"},"description":"Vietnam's ancient capital on the Red River, blending centuries of history with vibrant street culture, French colonial architecture, and bustling markets. It's the natural entry point to Northwest Vietnam and offers temples, museums, water puppetry, and exceptional street food."},{"rank":2,"name":"Ho Chi Minh City","placeId":"ho_chi_minh_city","regionId":"southeast","regionName":"Southeast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1705253920175-8df4e2408113?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIbyUyMENoaSUyME1pbmglMjBDaXR5JTIwc2t5bGluZSUyMG5pZ2h0fGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM4ODcwOTN8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Etienne Girardet"},"description":"Vietnam's largest city and economic hub, featuring colonial architecture, bustling markets, and vibrant street life. Essential for experiencing modern Vietnam and visiting the War Remnants Museum and Reunification Palace."},{"rank":3,"name":"Ha Long Bay","placeId":"ha_long_bay","regionId":"red_river_delta","regionName":"Red River Delta","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1570611322923-06a5e9fd42c1?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIYSUyMExvbmclMjBCYXklMjBsaW1lc3RvbmUlMjBrYXJzdHN8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzg4MTc3NXww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Thanti Riess"},"description":"A UNESCO World Heritage Site featuring thousands of limestone karsts rising from emerald waters, Ha Long Bay is Vietnam's most iconic natural wonder. Visitors can cruise among the dramatic islands, explore hidden caves, and swim in secluded lagoons."},{"rank":4,"name":"Hoi An","placeId":"hoi_an","regionId":"south_central","regionName":"South Central Coast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1526139334526-f591a54b477c?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIb2klMjBBbiUyMFZpZXRuYW18ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4NDAzNDM1MXww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Chris Slupski"},"description":"A charming ancient town with well-preserved buildings featuring Vietnamese, Chinese, and French architectural influences, and famous for its lantern-lit streets and tailor shops. It attracts visitors seeking a slower pace and cultural immersion away from Vietnam's larger cities."},{"rank":5,"name":"Da Nang","placeId":"da_nang","regionId":"south_central","regionName":"South Central Coast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1559592413-7cec4d0cae2b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxEYSUyME5hbmclMjBWaWV0bmFtfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMzQzNTN8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Andreea Popa"},"description":"A modern coastal city serving as Vietnam's third-largest port and a hub for central Vietnam tourism, with access to nearby beaches and mountains. It has grown rapidly as a destination for business travelers and beachgoers visiting nearby attractions."},{"rank":6,"name":"Phu Quoc Island","placeId":"phu_quoc","regionId":"mekong_delta","regionName":"Mekong Delta","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1572572216428-91def7b78278?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQaHUlMjBRdW9jJTIwaXNsYW5kJTIwYmVhY2h8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzg4NjkxOHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"allPhoto Bangkok"},"description":"A picturesque island in the Gulf of Thailand known for pristine beaches, seafood restaurants, and lush hills, famous for its fish sauce production. It combines tropical relaxation with local culture and outdoor activities like snorkeling and hiking."},{"rank":7,"name":"Sapa","placeId":"sapa","regionId":"northwest","regionName":"Northwest","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1694152491695-eb07510ba707?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTYXBhJTIwcmljZSUyMHRlcnJhY2VzJTIwbW91bnRhaW5zfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM4ODE1Nzh8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Denis Sobnakov"},"description":"A stunning mountain town in the Hoang Lien Son range at 1,600m elevation, famous for its terraced rice paddies, ethnic minority villages, and cool climate. It's the gateway to trekking through H'mong and other tribal settlements, offering some of Vietnam's most iconic landscapes and cultural experiences."},{"rank":8,"name":"Hue","placeId":"hue","regionId":"north_central","regionName":"North Central Coast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504457047772-27faf1c00561?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIdWUlMjBWaWV0bmFtfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMzQzODN8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Ruslan Bardash"},"description":"Vietnam's ancient imperial capital, home to the Citadel and royal tombs of the Nguyen Dynasty, showcasing feudal Vietnamese architecture and history. History buffs and cultural tourists visit to explore the nation's royal heritage and understand Vietnamese imperial traditions."},{"rank":9,"name":"Mekong Delta","placeId":"mekong_delta","regionId":"southeast","regionName":"Southeast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519458686549-d8ecac193cf9?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNZWtvbmclMjBEZWx0YSUyMGZsb2F0aW5nJTIwbWFya2V0fGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM4ODcwOTV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Anne Lin"},"description":"A vast network of rivers, canals, and islands producing Vietnam's rice and fruit, with a distinctly rural character and unique boat-based culture. Visit for floating markets, fruit orchards, and traditional village experiences."},{"rank":10,"name":"Nha Trang","placeId":"nha_trang","regionId":"south_central","regionName":"South Central Coast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1533002832-1721d16b4bb9?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxOaGElMjBUcmFuZyUyMGJlYWNoJTIwVmlldG5hbXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzODg2NzU0fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Huy"},"description":"Vietnam's premier beach resort city with a long crescent bay, vibrant seafood restaurants, and water sports infrastructure. It's the main hub of the South Central Coast offering diving, island tours, and a lively nightlife scene."}]}